// {1}{G} sorcery: "draw a card. Convoke." Pins the per-pip alternative-payment
// hook (PayPips) end to end: convoke lets a generic pip be paid by tapping a
// creature you control, and a colored pip by tapping a creature of that color
// ([CR#702.51a]) — "rather than pay that mana", without lowering the {2} mana
// value ([CR#202.3,702.51b]). No real convoke spell is canonized yet whose
// non-cost effect ("draw a card") is this minimal; the mock isolates the pip
// hook from any other mechanic. Per plugins/testing/README.md, canonize a real
// convoke spell and delete this once one lands.
//
// The convoke static is spelled DIRECTLY as two `PayPips` rows (the keyword
// macro sugar is exercised on the canon card) so the engine test does not
// depend on the keyword layer.
Normal(
    name: "Sorcery Convoke Draw",
    mana_cost: [Generic(1), Green],
    types: [Sorcery],
    abilities: [
        Spell(effect: Draw(1)),
        Static(effects: [
            PayPips(Generic, TapToPay(AllOf([Creature, ControlledBy(Ref(You))]))),
            PayPips(Colored(Green), TapToPay(AllOf([Creature, ColorIs(Green), ControlledBy(Ref(You))]))),
        ]),
    ],
)
